### Sample

::: {.callout-note collapse="true"}
## Saturation–coefficient degeneracy

The `b * saturation(lam * x)` parameterization creates a funnel-shaped degeneracy between the coefficient and saturation steepness.
This can cause divergences and max tree depth warnings.
Consider tighter priors, reparameterization, or a non-centered saturation formulation if sampling is difficult.
:::

