### Specify and fit the model

The `pooling` argument controls the hierarchical structure:

- `"intercept": True` gives each region its own baseline sales level
- `"slopes": ["tv", "digital"]` gives each region its own media coefficients, partially pooled toward a shared mean

::: {#7c421b06 .cell execution_count=40}
``` {.python .cell-code}
spec = """
sales ~ tv + digital + trend
"""

model = pathmc.model(
    spec,
    data=df,
    panel={"unit": "region", "time": "week"},
    pooling={"intercept": True, "slopes": ["tv", "digital"]},
)
```
:::


